Sentencas: A method for the rapid fabrication of homogeneous potential interconnect alloys from metal oxide precursors and evaluation of their thermal expansion mismatch to solid oxide fuel cells is described.
Titulo: Interconnect thermal expansion matching to solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Pastes of metal oxide powders were extruded into honeycomb geometries and sintered in hydrogen.
Titulo: Interconnect thermal expansion matching to solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Thermal expansion mismatch was evaluated based on heating with a zero-mismatch at room temperature, and on cooling with zero-mismatch temperatures at 600 or 1100 degrees C.
Titulo: Interconnect thermal expansion matching to solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The non-linear expansion behavior of Fe-Ni invar alloys resulted in different compositions being optimum, based on the assumed zero-mismatch temperature.
Titulo: Interconnect thermal expansion matching to solid oxide fuel cells
